Přindiš, Prskavec and Fišerová advanced safely to the semifinals of the World Championships
Kayakers Vít Přindiš and Jiří Prskavec and canoeist Tereza Fišerová advanced safely to the semifinals of the World Water Slalom Championships in Seu d'Urgell. Přindiš was fourth in Friday's qualification, Prskavec fifth and Fišerová eighth. The other three Czech representatives will strive for a semi-final start in Spain in the afternoon corrective qualifying race.
Vavřinec Hradilek did not succeed from the strong national group of kayakers, who at the very beginning of the ride received a 50-second penalty for incorrectly passing the goal. Přindiš and Prskavec, on the other hand, can now rest and concentrate on Sunday's semifinals.
"I set a goal for the first ride in my thirties, which I did. Not that I didn't care how I ended up, because it starts very early in the morning on Sunday, so I was hoping to be a little higher to get better starting position, "said Přindiš, praising the well-being in the Seu. "Before the patrol race, I felt the worst in 14 days since we were here. But then it was good during the race and better again today. It's beautiful here all the time, nice races, the spectators came, so fine," he smiled.
Sparkler was also satisfied. "In qualifying you don't want to make an unnecessary mistake. I didn't do well in the first goals. Then I drove well in the middle, without any problems and I knew I had a run, so the second mistake came when I wanted to go straight down and turned my head. "Overall, I can't be dissatisfied. The form is, we'll see how it goes," said this year's overall winner of the World Cup.
Both representatives praised themselves that they would go to the start on Sunday at the end of the semifinal block. "I'm not a morning bird, it's also cold here in the morning, and when you're here at eight, it wants a jacket and a sweatshirt," Přindiš said. "Overall, the semifinals take an hour and a half, which is a pretty good difference in terms of sleep," Prskavec agreed.
Of the three Czech singkano players, only Fišerová succeeded, Eva Říhová finished two places behind the twenties, Kateřina Havlíčková was 35. "I went down the upper part according to my ideas, The track I wanted to take. I made two pokes and I am just behind the winner with pure time. I have a good starting position for the semifinals, "Fišerová praised herself.
