Annex No. 9 / Acceptance procedure
The items below are for inspirational purposes only. This appendix must be formulated precisely and exhaustively by the project manager.
Upgrade Delivery
Acceptance Criteria for the Upgrade Delivery to initiate the Acceptance Procedure
Delivery of an incremental version of those parts of the Application in the form of executable codes to which the Upgrade applies
Delivery of the current version of the Functional Specification and Documentation of those parts of the Application to which the Upgrade applies
Successful execution of the Upgrade installation on the UAT environment according to the installation procedure, while the installation is performed by the Client's employee with the assistance of the Contractor's employees
Successful demonstration of Changes and Incidents included in the Upgrade, where the demonstration will be performed by the Contractor's employees and will be marked as successful if 80% of the demonstrated functionality runs smoothly.
Acceptance Criteria for the Upgrade Delivery to perform the Acceptance Procedure
Successful completion of the UAT (by implementing all relevant test scenarios), whereby the UATs are terminated as successful if the delivered Upgrade contains a maximum of the following number of unresolved Incidents:
TA incident: 0 (none)
TB incident: 3 (three)
TC category incident: 10 (ten)
Successful execution of business critical scenarios in a UAT environment, with no business critical scenario reporting a TA, TB, or TC incident
The Upgrade Delivery Acceptance Procedure may be terminated even if the number of unresolved UAT Incidents at one time that are defects in the Application or Documentation reaches or exceeds the following numbers of unresolved Incidents:
TA category incident: 5 (five)
TB incident: 10 (ten)
TC category incident: 30 (thirty)
Patch delivery
