Annex 12 / Safety rules
1. Definitions of terms
1.1 For the purposes of this Annex, the following terms and phrases have the meanings given below:
A security incident means any breach of the confidentiality, integrity or availability of Information Assets.
Information asset means any information, processes, hardware or software components that (1) support the business activities of the Authorized Entity, or (2) have value for the Authorized Entity, or (3) whose disclosure, unauthorized change or unavailability has a negative impact on the Authorized Entity. .
Contractor's Persons means persons who directly or indirectly participate in the performance of the subject of this Contract, including persons of the Contractor's subcontractors.
Authorized Entity Environment means the premises in which the Authorized Entity carries out its business activities and the information and communication systems used by the Authorized Entity and which contain Information Assets.
2. Personnel security
2.1 None of the Contractor's Persons:
2.1.1 does not have an entry in the criminal record;
2.1.2 has not been convicted of an intentional criminal offense in the past and is not prosecuted during the performance of the subject of this Agreement,
2.2 If the Contractor finds the Contractor's non-compliance with the above rules, he must immediately inform the Client thereof. The Client is entitled to demand that such a person no longer participate in the implementation of work arising from the subject of this Agreement, directly or indirectly, and is entitled to demand from the Contractor the provision of adequate compensation.
2.3 The Contractor shall provide the Client with a complete list of persons of the Contractor. The Contractor undertakes to inform the Client about changes in the staffing of the performance of this Contract in advance.
2.4 Persons of the Contractor:
2.4.1 must be familiar with these safety rules,
2.4.2 have all the necessary tests and attestations that result from the law or the requirements of the regulator for the type of work that they are to perform in connection with the performance of this Agreement,
2.4.3 are the Contractor of regular training in the areas of information security.
2.5 The Contractor's Persons may not enter the Environment of the Authorized Entity under the influence of addictive, narcotic or psychotropic substances or bring weapons, explosives, flammables, warfare agents, poisons, radioactive and toxic substances, or any other substance endangering human life and / or health.
3. Physical security
3.1 Access of the Contractor's Persons to the Environment of the Authorized Entity is permitted only if their presence is necessary for the performance of work duties arising from this Agreement.
3.2 The Contractor's persons always move in the Environment of the Authorized Entity accompanied by a responsible employee of the Client.
3.3 Free movement of the Contractor's Persons in the Environment of the Authorized Entity is permitted only if a personal access card has been issued to the given person. The Contractor's person may not further lend the access card to third parties or allow third parties access to the Environment of the Authorized Entity.
3.4 In the event of loss of the access card or in case of suspicion of loss of the access card, the Contractor is obliged to immediately inform the Client.
3.5 Without undue delay after the completion of the work arising from this Agreement or after the termination of this Agreement, or if further physical access of the Contractor's Persons to the Environment of the Authorized Entity is no longer necessary, the Client shall ensure that all Contractor Persons return the borrowed access cards to the Client.
3.6 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor Person may not remove any Information Assets from the Environment of the Authorized Entity via a storage medium.
4. Identification and authentication of the Contractor's Persons in the Environment of the Authorized Entity
4.1 The Contractor's persons are assigned only accounts enabling unambiguous identification of the user and only with such authorizations as are strictly necessary for the performance of their work duties arising from this Agreement.
4.2 Routine work is performed by the Contractor under non-privileged accounts, he uses accounts with administrator rights only in necessary cases.
4.3 Persons of the Contractor may not access the Internet if they work under an account with administrator rights or with applications that are running under administrator rights.
4.4 Inactive accounts of the Contractor's Persons are proactively reported by the Contractor to the Client.
4.5 Shared accounts are used by the Contractor only with the prior written consent of the Client.
4.6 In case of disclosure of the password or in case of suspicion of disclosure of the password, the Contractor must immediately ensure the change or blocking of the password.
5. Handling of certificates
5.1 Access to certificates (logical and physical) will be granted only to those Persons of the Contractor for whom this access is necessary for the performance of their job duties.
5.2 Without the written consent of the Client, the Contractor may not provide or make available the certificates to third parties.
5.3 After their installation, the certificates may be stored only in a secure repository in places where their storage is necessary for the performance of this Agreement, and all other copies shall be destroyed in a manner that prevents their renewal.
5.4 If possible, the private key of the certificate must be set as non-exportable. The private key of the certificate must always be protected by a strong password and must not be stored in unencrypted form.
5.5 The Contractor undertakes to immediately inform the Client of the loss or suspicion of loss of confidentiality of the private key of the certificate.
6. Management of Information Assets
6.1 Work with Information Assets is limited to places that preclude the observation of sensitive information by unauthorized persons. Specifically, it is forbidden to work with Information Assets in public transport, in public places and in places where there is a risk of observation from industrial cameras.
6.2 Upon completion of the work arising from this Contract, the Contractor shall without undue delay return or remove all Information Assets stored in the Contractor's environment, if the possession of this information is not required by the laws of the Czech Republic. This applies to both electronic and paper documentation. The removal of Information Assets must be done in a way that prevents their restoration.
6.3 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor may not provide access to the Information Assets to any third parties who are not entitled to participate in the performance of this Agreement.
6.4 The Contractor is obliged to ensure adequate security of the computer technology on which the Information Assets are stored, processed or transmitted. In connection with the Information Assets, the Contractor shall ensure that in the Contractor's environment:
6.4.1 tools are used to encrypt disks, folders or files so that unauthorized access to Information Assets is excluded,
6.4.2 tools are used for detection and removal of malicious code with the setting of regular updating of the database of malicious code signatures with a frequency not exceeding one week and appropriate processes of supervision, logging and response to a positive finding of malicious code are set up,
6.4.3 the processes of updating security patches of software components are defined, set up, executed and monitored in an interval not exceeding one month from the release of patches,
6.4.4 the Internet environment is separated by a firewall, which is connected to the surveillance and the Contractor's Persons use exclusively encrypted VPN connection during remote access, preventing unauthorized eavesdropping and change of transmitted communication.
6.5 If the Information Assets are transferred by the Contractor outside the premises of the Authorized Entity, the Contractor is obliged to pay close attention to the physical security of these assets and to keep these Information Assets under constant supervision. The Contractor is obliged to follow the safety and operating instructions of the hardware manufacturer on which the Information Assets are processed.
7. Work in the Environment of the Authorized Entity
7.1 The Contractor is obliged to become acquainted with and act in accordance with the standard of classification of Information Assets, if the Client provides it.
7.2 In the case of hardware owned and managed by the Client or hardware that, including its configuration, has been approved in advance by the Client, the Contractor may not make changes to the configuration of this hardware not approved by the Client. In particular, the Contractor may not make changes to the security configuration of the hardware. For each hardware installed in this way, the process of applying security patches must be explicitly and formally defined, including the responsibilities arising from the roles within the process.
7.3 Without the prior written consent of the Client, the Contractor may not install or run any software not approved by the Client in advance.
7.4 Without the written consent of the Client, the Contractor is not entitled to perform any testing of physical or logical security or any type of control mechanisms of the Authorized Entity.
7.5 The Contractor may not manipulate the audit records in any way.
7.6 The Contractor's persons are not authorized to work with software, hardware or data content that is not directly related to the performance of this Agreement.
7.7 Persons of the Contractor may not perform any activities that harm other natural or legal persons, including sending unsolicited emails, sending fraudulent emails, distributing malicious code or participating in attacks in order to exclude the availability of services.
7.8 The Client logs all steps performed by the Contractor's Persons and keeps a record of them for a period of 3 years.
7.9 Without the written consent of the Client, the Contractor's Persons may not connect their own storage devices to any computer equipment of the Authorized Entity.
7.10 At the provided workplace, the Contractor's Persons are obliged to ensure during the period of physical absence:
7.10.1 cleanliness and order so that the workplace can be used safely;
7.10.2 adequate physical security of all Information Assets;
7.10.3 logical locking of access to the Information Assets so that unauthorized access to these Information Assets cannot occur.
7.11 The Contractor's persons are not entitled to install a device enabling remote eavesdropping or to make any audio or video recording without the prior written consent of the Client.
8. Crisis management
8.1 Persons of the Contractor are obliged to prevent the occurrence of crisis situations (eg fire, explosion, flood, etc.) and situations in which personal injury or damage to the property of the Authorized Person may occur.
8.2 In the event of a crisis situation, the Contractor's Person, who is physically present at the scene, is obliged, without exception and delay, to comply with the regulations and directives valid in the given locality and to obey the instructions for evacuation and protection of persons. This also applies to the case of exercise.
8.3 In the event of crisis management, the Contractor's Person is obliged to immediately obey the instructions of the Client's crisis manager.
9. Security incident reporting
9.1 If the Contractor identifies a security incident, he is obliged to immediately report it to the tool https://helpdesk.jtfg.com (phone: +420 221 710 911).
