Last year, the District Court in Svitavy first found the woman guilty of torturing the entrusted person and endangering the child's upbringing. She formed a strong, even symbiotic bond with her daughter, even in a situation where she was to be entrusted to her father.
The result was a pathological fixation on the mother and a markedly negative relationship with the father. The situation marked the emotional development of her daughter, who was even hospitalized. She threatened self-harm if she was handed over to her father's care.
The Svitavy court sentenced the mother two years in prison with a two-year suspended sentence. However, the Pardubice branch of the regional court acquitted the woman in the appellate proceedings, it is said that this is not a criminal offense. The same verdict was repeated by the regional court even after the Supreme Court had once ordered it to decide again.
The regional court stated that situations where one parent manipulates a child towards the other are by no means exceptional. It is resolved in custody proceedings, or with the help of psychologists or youth social protection bodies. Only in exceptional cases is criminal law the solution.
