Trump is considering canceling Chinese stocks in the United States
The administration of US President Donald Trump is considering revoking the license of Chinese companies to trade on the stock markets in the United States. An informed source told Reuters today. Such a move would be a radical escalation of trade tensions between the United States and China. The shares of the companies in question on the New York Stock Exchange immediately went down after the report and withdrew the entire market.
The withdrawal of shares would be part of a broader effort to limit US investment in China, the source added. He confirmed the Bloomberg report, which shortly before caused a shock on the financial markets. Shares of Chinese companies Alibaba Group Holding, JD.com, Pinduoduo, Baidu, Vipshop Holdings, Baozun and IQIYI lost two to four percent.
According to government data from February, the shares of 156 Chinese companies are traded on the US stock exchanges Nasdaq and NYSE. There are also at least 11 state-owned enterprises among them.
Bloomberg pointed out that a precise mechanism has not yet been developed to ensure the withdrawal of shares of Chinese companies from US stock exchanges. A possible plan would have to be approved by Trump, who, however, gave the green light to negotiations on the matter.
China and the United States have been waging a trade war for more than a year, during which they impose tariffs on each other. The dispute between the two countries has negative effects on the world economy and raises fears of a recession in the global economy. Washington is using tariffs to force Beijing to change trade practices and reduce China's trade surplus with the United States.
According to the CNBC television server, trade negotiations between the USA and China should be resumed on October 10. Its goal is to end the trade war.
Former French President Chirac will be buried on Monday, with a public pieta on Sunday
The funeral of former French President Jacques Chirac, who died Thursday at the age of 86, will take place on Monday evening at the Montparnasse Cemetery in Paris. The French media reports with reference to Chirac's family. The ceremony will be private.
