Ankle valgosity is a congenital defect that affects five to ten percent of children. It is usually treated with intensive exercise. The researchers are trying to help these children even more, so they have developed special footwear that should significantly speed up the treatment.
"We have two prototype shoes that will be worn by healthy children and children with diagnoses to map the effect in both groups. Participation in the research will have no risks for children and the measurement will be completely painless," explains Marta Gimunová, head of research at the Faculty of Sports Studies. HIM.
Parents of both groups of children can register for the study via the website, where the registration form and all information are available.
Researchers are looking for fifty children with a diagnosis and fifty healthy children. Half of each group will always wear medical footwear and half will not.
"The moment parents should register their child is when they take the first separate steps, such as the furniture they hold on to when trying to walk. Participating in the research involves three measurements within seven months of the child's first steps. , each lasting about 20 minutes, in half of the participants it also includes wearing the tested shoes, "Gimunová points out.
The opening of the Pumpkin World delayed the ripening of pumpkins
Nová Ves u Leštiny (Havlíčkobrodsko) - The farm in Nová Ves u Leštiny in Havlíčkobrodsko today opened the Pumpkin World for more than a month. Decorations made of thousands of freshly harvested pumpkins are dominated by massive orange pyramids in the garden. The autumn event, which is becoming a tradition, starts a week later this year, as pumpkins have matured longer on the surrounding seven hectares of fields of the Pipek family. There are still many of them in the field, Jaroslava Pipková told ČTK today.
Pipek grows many types of pumpkins, but the weather has not been good for the last two years. This year's harvest was delayed and some species did not come out. "As usual, we have plenty of orange pumpkins for Halloween, but some species didn't work for connoisseurs," Pipková said. Nevertheless, you can choose from several types on the farm, from the already mentioned large pumpkins suitable for carving and digging decorations through pumpkins for cooking hokaido or elongated "spaghetti" to decorative pumpkins of various colors and shapes.
Growing pumpkins is laborious. Farmers manually dig up plants and harvest their fruits, cutting them from the stem of the pumpkin with scissors. The Pumpkin World has been open to Pipek regularly since 2010, previous years have attracted thousands of people. The decoration of pumpkins is complemented by attractions made of straw or a maze of logs. Visitors will also see animals kept on the farm. It will be open daily until November 3.
Details of the event can be found on the farm's website, where growers also offer some recipes for pumpkin dishes, such as pumpkin muffins or juice. Visitors themselves tell them about other possibilities of preparing pumpkins in the kitchen. "A lot of cookbooks have tried their own recipes, and we also get inspired," Pipková said. She noted that some housewives also treat pumpkins to pickles like cucumbers.
