An attempt to assassinate a hairdresser in Hořice took place in February 2013. The Hradec Králové Public Prosecutor's Office accused him of a then twenty-year-old student at the Nečesaný grammar school. The prosecution claimed that he hit a woman in the head several times with a log and then took over ten thousand crowns from her. Her son found a seriously injured woman, her life was saved by doctors from the Hradec Králové hospital.
